What?

792
00:40:47,678 --> 00:40:48,679
Remember?

793
00:40:48,746 --> 00:40:50,981
The day I first met you.

794
00:40:51,982 --> 00:40:55,319
I wanted to show myself
in a wedding dress to my father soon.

795
00:40:56,187 --> 00:41:00,124
My mother passed away in the year
of the Great Hanshin earthquake.

796
00:41:00,191 --> 00:41:01,992
The Great Hanshin earthquake?

797
00:41:02,526 --> 00:41:05,396
When you don't know something,
you just Google it, like this.

798
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:06,430
See?

799
00:41:06,497 --> 00:41:08,799
What? Are you kidding me?

800
00:41:08,866 --> 00:41:10,935
1995? That's nine years from now.

801
00:41:11,569 --> 00:41:12,636
An earthquake that big?

802
00:41:13,537 --> 00:41:15,039
Huh, I see.

803
00:41:15,806 --> 00:41:17,007
I'll keep that in mind.

804
00:41:17,675 --> 00:41:22,379
When he found out
that your mother was his own daughter,

805
00:41:23,013 --> 00:41:24,315
he knew about her passing.

806
00:41:39,697 --> 00:41:40,531
What?

807
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:44,835
So he knew already

808
00:41:45,903 --> 00:41:48,038
and played along with our lies?

809
00:41:58,315 --> 00:41:59,149
I see.

810
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:02,887
I see.

811
00:42:05,256 --> 00:42:06,156
But I'm glad.

812
00:42:07,224 --> 00:42:10,427
I was able to become friendly with you,
patch things up,

813
00:42:11,362 --> 00:42:13,631
share some drinks, and hold my grandkid.

814
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:16,834
I get to enjoy all that in the future.

815
00:42:19,537 --> 00:42:20,738
I'm looking forward to it!

816
00:42:26,443 --> 00:42:27,278
So,

817
00:42:28,078 --> 00:42:28,913
where's my suit?

818
00:42:35,319 --> 00:42:36,153
Hey.

819
00:42:39,924 --> 00:42:40,758
Right.

820
00:42:41,425 --> 00:42:42,860
I'd brought it from Kobe.

821
00:42:43,627 --> 00:42:46,564
<i>This is the first suit</i>

822
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:49,333
<i>I tailored</i>

823
00:42:52,202 --> 00:42:56,240
<i>A suit</i>

824
00:42:56,307 --> 00:42:58,275
<i>For my father</i>

825
00:43:01,612 --> 00:43:04,582
<i>The first suit</i>

826
00:43:04,648 --> 00:43:07,318
<i>I am tailoring</i>

827
00:43:10,020 --> 00:43:13,791
<i>A suit</i>

828
00:43:14,358 --> 00:43:16,327
<i>For my father</i>

829
00:43:23,067 --> 00:43:25,970
<i>If your figure</i>

830
00:43:26,036 --> 00:43:29,773
<i>Is unchanged</i>

831
00:43:30,474 --> 00:43:34,445
<i>It's still the same</i>

832
00:43:34,945 --> 00:43:41,952
<i>It should suit you very well</i>

833
00:44:08,746 --> 00:44:09,680
Hey.

834
00:44:10,581 --> 00:44:11,482
What do you think?

835
00:44:12,616 --> 00:44:13,450
You look great.

836
00:44:18,622 --> 00:44:20,257
Of course, you do.

837
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:23,327
Dad made that suit.

838
00:44:30,934 --> 00:44:33,103
ICHIRO OGAWA

839
00:44:52,956 --> 00:44:54,191
You don't know? You're behind.

840
00:44:54,258 --> 00:44:55,893
-Is it behind the times?
-The topics and wording…

841
00:44:55,959 --> 00:44:57,061
They're like something from old stories.

842
00:44:57,127 --> 00:44:58,962
When geezers can't find
hope in the future,

843
00:44:59,029 --> 00:45:00,798
they start reminiscing about the past.

844
00:45:00,864 --> 00:45:03,033
The only one allowed to mock my dad

845
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:05,235
is me, his daughter.

846
00:45:05,736 --> 00:45:07,004
I'm back, Junko.

847
00:45:07,071 --> 00:45:07,905
Subtitle translation by: Ai Matsuoka

